hafod Example Scripts
=====================

These scripts demonstrate real-world usage of hafod (a scsh port for
Chez Scheme). Each script exercises different subsystems and can be run
safely -- they only read system state, create temp files in /tmp, and
run common Unix commands.

Running
-------

  From the project root:

    scheme --libdirs src --script examples/<name>.ss

  Or compile first for speed:

    make compile
    scheme --libdirs src --script examples/<name>.ss


Scripts
-------

  01-system-info.ss        System information and process state
  02-list-executables.ss   List all executables on PATH
  03-pipeline-demo.ss      Process notation, pipelines, redirections
  04-find-large-files.ss   Find large files using glob and file-info
  05-word-frequency.ss     Word frequency count using AWK macro
  06-log-analyzer.ss       Parse structured data with field splitters
  07-csv-processor.ss      CSV processing with infix-splitter
  08-regex-demo.ss         SRE regex matching, substitution, folding
  09-directory-tree.ss     Recursive directory listing with file types
  10-env-manager.ss        Environment variable manipulation
  11-temp-file-demo.ss     Temp file creation and I/O channels
  12-process-demo.ss       Fork, wait, signals, background processes
  13-file-renamer.ss       Rename files using regex patterns (dry-run)
  14-disk-usage.ss         Disk usage summary via pipelines
  15-backup-script.ss      Backup files to a temp directory


Features Exercised
------------------

  Process notation     run, &, exec-epf, ||, &&
  Pipelines            pipe, run/string, run/strings, run/port
  Redirections         <, >, >>, <<, =, -
  Run collectors       run/collecting, run/file, run/sexp
  File operations      file-info, directory-files, glob, create-temp-file
  File names           split-file-name, file-name-extension, resolve-file-name
  Environment          getenv, setenv, with-env, with-total-env, env->alist
  Process state        cwd, with-cwd, umask, with-umask, pid, user-uid
  Process mgmt         fork, wait, signal-process, process-sleep
  Delimited I/O        read-line, read-delimited, read-paragraph
  Field readers        field-splitter, infix-splitter, record-reader
  AWK macro            awk with patterns, ranges, state variables
  Regex (SRE)          rx, regexp-search, regexp-substitute/global
  Time/date            time, date, format-date
  User/group           user-info, group-info, home-directory
  System info          uname, system-name
  Temp files           create-temp-file, temp-file-channel
  Port collectors      port->string, port->string-list, port-fold
